MultiPixel Modding Technical Standards
Relimintor 

1. PURPOSE
This document defines the technical expectations for Mods, even before the
official API is released.

2. GENERAL PRINCIPLES
Mods must:
• be stable
• be safe
• not degrade performance
• not interfere with anti-cheat
• not modify executable code
• not modify network packets
• not introduce vulnerabilities

3. PROHIBITED TECHNIQUES
Mods may NOT:
• inject code
• patch memory
• modify bytecode
• alter network traffic
• bypass security checks
• use proxies or packet sniffers
• automate gameplay
• modify the launcher or client

4. FUTURE API EXPECTATIONS
The official API will:
• provide safe hooks
• prevent unsafe operations
• enforce sandboxing
• restrict access to sensitive systems

5. COMPATIBILITY REQUIREMENTS
Mods must:
• not break other mods
• not break servers
• not break client updates
• follow versioning rules

6. SUBMISSION REQUIREMENTS
Mod submissions must include:
• description
• version
• dependencies
• changelog
• safety notes
• performance notes

7. MULTIPIXEL RIGHTS
MultiPixel may:
• reject mods
• modify mods
• remove mods
• revoke approval
• enforce safety standards
